1 (33) "Registered business" means a business entity that owns or otherwise possesses
2 critical infrastructure and that is registered to do business in the state prior to the
3 declared state disaster or emergency;
4 (34)[(32)] "Resident" means an individual domiciled within this state or an individual
5 who is not domiciled in this state, but maintains a place of abode in this state and
6 spends in the aggregate more than one hundred eighty-three (183) days of the
7 taxable year in this state;
8 (35)[(33)] "S corporation" has the same meaning as in Section 1361(a) of the Internal
9 Revenue Code;
10 (36)[(34)] "State" means a state of the United States, the District of Columbia, the
11 Commonwealth of Puerto Rico, or any territory or possession of the United States;
12 (37)[(35)] "Taxable net income":
13 (a) In the case of corporations that are taxable in this state, means "net income" as
14 defined in subsection (24) of this section;
15 (b) In the case of corporations that are taxable in this state and taxable in another
16 state, means "net income" as defined in subsection (24) of this section and as
17 allocated and apportioned under KRS 141.120;
18 (c) For homeowners' associations as defined in Section 528(c) of the Internal
19 Revenue Code, means "taxable income" as defined in Section 528(d) of the
20 Internal Revenue Code. Notwithstanding the provisions of subsection (21) of
21 this section, the Internal Revenue Code sections referred to in this paragraph
22 shall be those code sections in effect for the applicable tax year; and
23 (d) For a corporation that meets the requirements established under Section 856
24 of the Internal Revenue Code to be a real estate investment trust, means "real
25 estate investment trust taxable income" as defined in Section 857(b)(2) of the
26 Internal Revenue Code, except that a captive real estate investment trust shall
27 not be allowed any deduction for dividends paid;
